cs.IT, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.NI, cs.SI. 

This paper deals with information theory and graph theory, which are both covered by cs.IT and cs.DM. The concept of capacity is also relevant to computer communication networks, which falls under cs.CC. The use of graphs and their properties in the analysis of the channel capacity suggests cs.NI as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on proving a conjecture using mathematical techniques makes cs.SI a plausible sub-category as well.
